Why this license, briefly:

- Standard MIT grants the permissions above (use, copy, modify, merge,
  publish, distribute, sublicense, sell) with the copyright and permission
  notices preserved.
- The attribution clause (clause 2) is a standard, common addition to MIT
  for solo portfolio projects. It requires downstream users to keep the
  author's name and contact URLs visible in their distribution. This is
  not a restriction on commercial use; it is a requirement that the
  authorship be acknowledged.
- The full text of standard MIT is in the public domain; the addition of
  the attribution clause above is the only material difference from a
  stock MIT license. SPDX classifies this as a custom license, not as
  standard MIT.
